.SH NAME
drm_wait_one_vblank \- wait for one vblank
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_wait_one_vblank
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pipe "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "pipe" 12
CRTC index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This waits for one vblank to pass on \fIpipe\fP, using the irq driver interfaces.
It is a failure to call this when the vblank irq for \fIpipe\fP is disabled, e.g.
due to lack of driver support or because the crtc is off.

This is the legacy version of \fBdrm_crtc_wait_one_vblank\fP.
